cs.GT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CR, cs.IT

The paper deals with game theory and algorithms, which are typically categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also mentions cryptographic hardness assumptions, which suggests a connection to cryptography, and hence cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests a connection to cs.CC (Computational Complexity), while the use of polynomial-time Turing machines suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the use of public-key encryption, which suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory).
